Page_0: "Such incompetence! Our hiring practices must be unbelievably wretched to allow such commoners to work here. I watch them day after day from my secret window as they gossip and gallivant around. Such unprofessionalism!

At the very least we have the best exhibits. Even the Wieldstrom doesn't boast the finest artifacts from Sunnyport. My little business arrangement is paying off well..."

Page_1: "Such a good thing I'm able to see everything that's going on. That is at least some measure of comfort. And oh how coming here relaxes me, where I might gaze upon my love. So perfect, so frail, the women today are but shadows of what they were in your time, Lady Isabella. The softest caress of your flesh is enough to make me forget this harsh business altogether."
